data <- read_csv('Madata.csv') %>%
  filter(F1 < 1500) %>% filter(Vowel != 'u') %>% group_by(Speaker) %>% mutate(F0_z = scale(F0)) %>% filter(F0_z > -2) %>%
  mutate_if(is.character, as.factor)

ggplot(data, aes(Mode, F0_z, colour = Mode)) +
  geom_violin() +
  geom_boxplot(width=0.2) +
  geom_jitter(alpha=0.05) +
  facet_grid(~Gen)

ggplot(durData, aes(Mode, Duration, colour = Mode)) +
  geom_violin() +
  geom_boxplot(width=0.2) +
  geom_jitter(alpha=0.05) +
  facet_grid(~Long)

filter(data, Gen == "M") %>%
ggplot(aes(F2, F1, colour = Mode)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.2) +
  stat_ellipse() +
  scale_x_reverse() +
  scale_y_reverse() + 
  facet_wrap(~Vowel, scales = 'free') +
  labs(title = "F1-F2 vowel plots for male speakers in soft, neutral and loud speech modes")
## Warning: Removed 13 rows containing non-finite values (stat_ellipse).
